<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>HACKME Login</title>
  <style>
    body {
      background: #181c20;
      color: #f8f8f2;
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-height: 100vh;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .login-container {
      background: #23272b;
      padding: 2rem 2.5rem;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
      min-width: 320px;
      max-width: 90vw;
    }
    h1 {
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      color: #50fa7b;
      text-align: center;
    }
    label {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      color: #8be9fd;
    }
    input[type="text"], input[type="password"] {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 5px;
      border: 1px solid #44475a;
      background: #282a36;
      color: #f8f8f2;
      margin-top: 0.3rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    button {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 0.7rem;
      background: #50fa7b;
      color: #282a36;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: bold;
      cursor: pointer;
      margin-top: 0.5rem;
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }
    button:hover {
      background: #40c96b;
    }
    .message {
      color: #ff5555;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .tip {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      color: #f1fa8c;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    code {
      background: #44475a;
      color: #f1fa8c;
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="login-container">
    <h1>HACKME Login</h1>
    <% if (message) { %>
      <!-- VULNERABLE: XSS in error message -->
      <div class="message"><%- message %></div>
    <% } %>
    <form method="POST" action="/login">
      <label>Username:
        <input type="text" name="username" autocomplete="username" />
      </label>
      <label>Password:
        <input type="password" name="password" autocomplete="current-password" />
      </label>
      <button type="submit">Login</button>
    </form>
    <div class="tip">
      Try SQL Injection: <code>' OR '1'='1</code><br>
      <a href="/help" style="color:#8be9fd;text-decoration:underline;">How to exploit vulnerabilities?</a> |
      <a href="/register" style="color:#8be9fd;text-decoration:underline;">Register a new user</a> |
      <a href="/change-password" style="color:#8be9fd;text-decoration:underline;">Change password</a>
      <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;font-size:0.95rem;color:#f1fa8c;text-align:left;">
        <b>Vulnerability Explanations:</b><br>
        <ul style="margin:0 0 0 1.2em;padding:0;">
          <li><b>SQL Injection:</b> The login form directly inserts your input into a SQL query, allowing you to bypass authentication or extract data.</li>
          <li><b>XSS:</b> Error messages and dashboard display your input without sanitization, so scripts you enter will run in the browser.</li>
          <li><b>User Enumeration:</b> Try <a href="/login-verbose">/login-verbose</a> for different error messages for username vs. password.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
